total length: 16.3–16.9; head length: 2.1–2.3; head width: 3.1–3.3; pronotal width: 10.2–10.8; abdominal width: 8.7–9.0; length of antennal segments. I: 0.7–0.8; II: 1.9–2.1; III: 1.2–1.3; IV: 4.0–4.2; V: 5.0; interocular distance: 1.4–1.7; scutellum length: 7.8–7.9; scutellum width: 5.7–5.8; pronotal length: 3.4–3.7.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2B665313161D90344E26890FE6F1D9B" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FA1336BA3161D90344E26890FE6F1D9B" blockId="28.[151,1437,1246,2030]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90344E26890FEDE1C27" bold="true" box="[199,322,1534,1561]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum without solid black stripe. Pronotum with a transversal solid black stripe covering almost entire posterior margin (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90346976B4DFC871C03" box="[690,795,1571,1597]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
); posterolateral angle developed laterally, slightly short- er than interocular distance. Connexivum completely green (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90347686B29FC2B1C5F" box="[845,951,1607,1633]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
). Anterolateral margin of pronotum gently curved and punctured. Anterior margin of scutellum concolorous (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90347A76B05FC761CBB" box="[898,1002,1643,1669]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
). Black spot of costal margin reaching approximately 1/3 of corial extension. Dorsal surface of abdomen yellow or green with brown longitudinal stripe mesially. Ventrally apex of pseudosutures without rounded dark spots (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D903479E6BDDFBBA1CF3" box="[955,1062,1715,1741]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1749,1774]" captionTargetBox="[181,1415,196,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[151,1436,181,1723]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. brachyacanthus A–B; H. infulatus C–D; H. leptacanthus E–F; H. tragelaphus G–H (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677909" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677909/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 20D</figureCitation>
). Male (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90340A16BDDFB481CF3" box="[1156,1236,1715,1741]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1727,1752]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,323,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,306,1702]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. H. infulatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677897/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
A–C). Pygophore with dorsal rim concave (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D903459C6BB9FDBF1CCF" box="[441,547,1751,1777]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1727,1752]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,323,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,306,1702]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. H. infulatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677897/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Paramere with anterior lobe very short and truncate; posterior lobe short and acuminate (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D903453F6B95FE1E1D2B" box="[282,386,1787,1813]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1727,1752]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,323,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,306,1702]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. H. infulatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677897/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with moderately separated tufts of setae, compared with widely separated tufts of setae in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90344D26A4EFE331D07" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[247,431,1822,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxyacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90344D26A4EFE331D07" bold="true" box="[247,431,1822,1850]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. oxyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; posterior face ogival and flat (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90347386A71FC191D07" box="[797,901,1823,1849]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1727,1752]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,323,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,306,1702]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. H. infulatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677897/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions little developed, flat, and acuminate (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D903455E6A2DFE7E1D63" box="[379,482,1859,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1727,1752]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,323,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,306,1702]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. H. infulatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677897/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
). Female (
<figureCitation id="62972A3F3161D90346736A2DFD231D63" box="[598,703,1859,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1727,1752]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,323,1677]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[151,1436,306,1702]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 14. H. infulatus. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. E—metasternal process (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677897/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites 8 posterior margin straight; sutural border contiguous; inner angle not developed. Gonocoxites 9 slightly convex; margin rounded. Laterotergites 9 barely surpassing sclerite uniting laterotergites 8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2B665313161D90244E26AC0FBBE1AC5" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FA1336BA3161D90244E26AC0FBBE1AC5" blockId="28.[151,1437,1246,2030]" lastBlockId="29.[151,1436,153,287]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="430" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90344E26AC0FED31DF7" bold="true" box="[199,335,1966,1993]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">Comments.</emphasis>
Like in 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D90345936ADEFDF21DF7" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[438,622,1966,1994]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oxyacanthus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D90345936ADEFDF21DF7" bold="true" box="[438,622,1966,1994]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">H. oxyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the complement of 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393161D903477C6ADEFC4E1DF7" authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1904" box="[857,978,1967,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infulata">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83161D903477C6ADEFC4E1DF7" box="[857,978,1967,1993]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="429">E. infulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
description was published ahead of the original description of the species (
<bibRefCitation id="9E3D4B4B3161D90346026ABDFD4F1DD3" author="Breddin, G." box="[551,723,2003,2029]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" pagination="135 - 153" refId="ref24439" refString="Breddin, G. (1904 a) Beitrage zur Systematik der Rhynchoten. Sitzungsberichte der Gesellschaft Naturforschender Freunde zu Berlin, 1904, 135 - 153." type="journal article" year="1904">Breddin 1904a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E3D4B4B3161D90346C56ABDFCB51DD3" author="Breddin, G." box="[736,809,2003,2029]" pageId="28" pageNumber="429" pagination="49 - 50" refId="ref24467" refString="Breddin, G. (1904 b) Neue Rhynchotenausbeute aus Sud-Amerika (fortsetzung). Societas Entomologica, 19 (7), 49 - 50." type="journal article" year="1904">1904b</bibRefCitation>
, 14 June and 1 July, respectively). In both publications Breddin considered the species related to 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393160D90246436DF4FC9E1A8D" authorityName=", Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[614,770,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadridens">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83160D90246436DF4FDEB1A8D" box="[614,631,154,179]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83160D90246A16DF7FC9E1A8D" box="[644,770,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">quadridens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393160D90247356DF4FC441A8D" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Campos &amp; Mendonca &amp; Cunha &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[784,984,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infulatus">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83160D90247356DF4FC441A8D" box="[784,984,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">Hypoxys infulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily separable by projected humeral angles and connexivum uniformly green, without dark spots on segments III–VI (short humeral angles and connexivum spotted in 
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83160D90245506D8FFD861AC5" box="[373,538,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">
<taxonomicName id="3DAC4D393160D90245506D8FFD931AC5" box="[373,527,224,251]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriden">
<emphasis id="C8D8EAA83160D90245506D8FFD931AC5" bold="true" box="[373,527,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="430">H. quadriden</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s
</emphasis>
). The male is described here for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
